<title>SINGAPORE: Adobe sees US$150 mln sales.</title>
<headline>Adobe sees US$150 mln sales.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-04-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>U.S. graphic editing software company, Adobe Systems Inc, said on Monday it expected revenue from Asia Pacific and Latin America to reach about US$150 million by year 2000.  </p>
<p>&quot;Asia Pacific and Latin America are now about three to four percent of total company's revenue,&quot; Graham Freeman, Adobe's vice president and general manager of Asia Pacific and Latin America told Reuters.</p>
<p>&quot;By year 2000, we would like to be about 15 percent of revenue, which would see us getting to about US$150 million across Asia Pacific and Latin America,&quot; he added.</p>
<p>Freeman said the company should achieve compound growth rate of about 40 to 45 percent over the next few years.</p>
<p>For the financial year ended November 29, 1996, Adobe recorded revenues of US$786.6 million.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703080)</p>
